<item>
            <title>[LU-14350] Only use wake_up_all() when necessary</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14350</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;wake_up_all() is only needed when there are threads doing an exclusive wait.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;wake_up() will wake up all non-exclusive threads, and at most one exclusive thread.&#160; When non-exclusive waits are used, it is sufficient and preferred to use wake_up() to&#160; wake them up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;wake_up_all() should be reserved for those cases where threads are waiting exclusively, and they all want to be woken up.&#160; Keeping it for the purpose only improve code readability.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
